# Unified Styling System Rule

## 🎯 Objective

Enforce the unified styling system across all new pages and components. This rule ensures consistent, maintainable styling that follows the established design tokens and patterns.

## 📋 Core Principles

### **ALWAYS Use Design Tokens**

- Use `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `border-primary` instead of hardcoded colors
- Use `bg-secondary`, `text-text-primary`, `text-text-secondary` for neutral elements
- Use `bg-success`, `bg-warning`, `bg-error`, `bg-info` for status indicators

### **NEVER Use Hardcoded Colors**

- ❌ `bg-blue-600`, `bg-green-600`, `bg-gray-50`
- ❌ `text-blue-600`, `text-gray-900`, `text-slate-800`
- ❌ `border-blue-500`, `border-gray-200`

### **Use Standard Component Patterns**

- Follow established patterns for cards, buttons, forms, typography
- Maintain consistent spacing and layout
- Use proper hover states and transitions

## 🎨 Required Patterns

### **Page Structure**

```jsx
<div className="bg-secondary min-h-screen">
  <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">Page Title</h1>
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### **Cards**

```jsx
<div className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 border border-border">
  <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Card Title</h2>
  <p className="text-text-secondary">Card content</p>
</div>
```

### **Primary Buttons**

```jsx
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-primary hover:bg-primary-hover text-white rounded transition-colors">
  Action Button
</button>
```

### **Secondary Buttons**

```jsx
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-secondary text-text-primary border border-border rounded hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
  Secondary Action
</button>
```

### **Form Elements**

```jsx
<input
  className="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-border rounded focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary focus:border-primary transition"
  placeholder="Enter text"
/>
```

### **Status Indicators**

```jsx
<span className="bg-success text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">
  Success
</span>
```

## 🔧 Implementation Rules

### **For New Components:**

1. **Import design tokens**: Ensure `../index.css` is imported
2. **Use semantic class names**: `bg-primary` not `bg-green-600`
3. **Follow spacing patterns**: Use consistent padding and margins
4. **Include hover states**: Always add hover variants for interactive elements
5. **Test accessibility**: Ensure proper contrast ratios

### **For Existing Components:**

1. **Migrate gradually**: Replace hardcoded colors with design tokens
2. **Maintain functionality**: Don't break existing features
3. **Test thoroughly**: Verify visual consistency
4. **Update documentation**: Keep style guides current

### **Color Mapping Reference**

```css
/* OLD → NEW */
bg-green-600 → bg-primary
bg-green-700 → bg-primary-hover
bg-blue-600 → bg-primary (for actions)
bg-blue-700 → bg-primary-hover
text-gray-900 → text-text-primary
text-gray-600 → text-text-secondary
text-blue-600 → text-primary
bg-gray-50 → bg-secondary
bg-slate-50 → bg-secondary
border-gray-200 → border-border
border-slate-200 → border-border
focus:ring-blue-500 → focus:ring-primary
focus:border-blue-500 → focus:border-primary
```

## 🎯 Brand Color Usage

### **Hyatt Brand Colors (For Hyatt-Specific Features Only)**

```jsx
// Hyatt orchestration features
<div className="bg-hyatt-blue hover:bg-hyatt-blue-hover">
  Hyatt Campaign
</div>

// Hyatt accent elements
<span className="text-hyatt-gold">Hyatt Brand</span>
```

### **General UI Colors (For System Features)**

```jsx
// Primary actions
<button className="bg-primary hover:bg-primary-hover">
  Save
</button>

// Secondary elements
<div className="bg-secondary text-text-primary">
  Content
</div>
```

## ⚠️ Common Mistakes to Avoid

### **❌ Don't Do This:**

```jsx
// Hardcoded colors
<button className="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700">
  Save
</button>

// Inconsistent patterns
<div className="bg-gray-50 p-4">
  <h1 className="text-slate-800">Title</h1>
</div>

// Missing hover states
<button className="bg-green-600 text-white">
  Action
</button>
```

### **✅ Do This Instead:**

```jsx
// Design tokens
<button className="bg-primary hover:bg-primary-hover text-white">
  Save
</button>

// Consistent patterns
<div className="bg-secondary p-4">
  <h1 className="text-text-primary">Title</h1>
</div>

// Proper hover states
<button className="bg-primary hover:bg-primary-hover text-white transition-colors">
  Action
</button>
```

## 🔍 Validation Checklist

Before committing any new component or page:

- [ ] All colors use design tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-primary`, etc.)
- [ ] No hardcoded color values (`bg-blue-600`, `text-gray-900`)
- [ ] Consistent spacing patterns used
- [ ] Hover states included for interactive elements
- [ ] Proper focus states for accessibility
- [ ] Component follows established patterns
- [ ] Visual consistency with existing components

## 📚 Reference Documentation

- [Unified Styling System Guide](../docs/frontend/STYLING_SYSTEM_GUIDE.md) - Complete styling system documentation

## 🚀 Best Practices

1. **Start with design tokens** - Always use `bg-primary` instead of hardcoded colors
2. **Follow established patterns** - Use the same structure for similar components
3. **Test in context** - Verify components work together visually
4. **Document changes** - Update style guides when adding new patterns
5. **Consider accessibility** - Ensure proper contrast and focus states
6. **Maintain consistency** - Use the same approach across all components

This rule ensures all new development follows the unified styling system and maintains visual consistency across the Hive Agent System.
